abstract = {In response to problems such as uneven resource allocation, insufficient environmental monitoring, and low production efficiency in marine ranch management, big data technology is introduced to improve the digital management level of marine ranches through real-time data collection and analysis, and to promote its transformation towards intelligent, precise and sustainable development. First, this study uses deep learning models to better integrate data from various sensors. analyzed the pain points in the existing marine ranching management system and identifies deficiencies in resource management, environmental monitoring, data collection and analysis. Secondly, it builded an intelligent management system based on a big data platform, integrating multi-dimensional information such as environmental monitoring data, aquaculture production data, and market demand data, and uses data mining technology to predict future trends. And also combined the Internet of Things and artificial intelligence technologies to achieve real-time data collection and intelligent decision-making support for marine ranches, thereby improving production benefits, optimizing resource allocation, and promoting management efficiency,ensemble learning methods are used to assist decision-making. Through data-driven intelligent management, not only the efficiency of industrial management and production benefits are improved, but also the dual goals of environmental protection and sustainable development are promoted.},
