abstract = {This paper introduces a method for real-time detection of static human hand gestures amidst complex backgrounds and within distances of up to 2.5 meters, utilizing TinyML technology on microcontroller units (MCUs) equipped with vision sensors. Emphasizing affordability, sustainability, and energy efficiency, our approach replaces costly edge devices with low-cost MCUs. Our two-stage Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) achieves over 92\% accuracy in detecting five static hand gestures. It reduces power consumption and computational resources by 99\% compared to sate-of-the-art methods, requiring only 120 KB RAM and 367 KB FLASH, compatible with ESP32-CAM boards costing less than 6 USD. Operating at 1 frame per second (FPS), our implementation is practical for real-world applications. Additionally, we integrate our system into a custom PCB setup featuring an ESP32-CAM board, relay module, and 2.4-inch TFT Display, enabling real-time gesture recognition for appliance control and display annotation. This research demonstrates the transformative potential of TinyML for low-cost, low-power, long-range gesture control systems, advancing applications in smart living, healthcare, and environmental sustainability.},
